restaurants. seminyak is home to many of the trendy independent options, and elsewhere on the island, the better five-star resorts have their own very high quality in-house restaurants with prices to match. at all but the cheapest local restaurants, it is normal for 10% government sales tax and 5% service charge to be added to your bill. some restaurants include this in the price, but most expressly state these plus plus terms. drink[edit][add listing] the balinese have nothing against a drink, and alcohol is widely available. however this doesn't mean that drunken behaviour is entirely acceptable. indonesia's most popular beer 